cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the integration of vehicular networks and cloud computing, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed architecture involves the integration of multiple computing nodes, which can be categorized under distributed computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the optimization of resource allocation to minimize power consumption, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The proposed Mixed Integer Linear Programming (MILP) model can be categorized under computational engineering. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the analysis of different assignment strategies and their impact on the utilization of resources, which can be considered as an information theory problem.
